		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Birmingham_Quran_manuscript.jpg" class="mw-file-description" title="Image 6Two leaves of an early Quranic manuscript in the Mingana Collection of Middle Eastern manuscripts of the University of Birmingham&#39;s Cadbury Research Library were discovered in 2015 as being dated between 568 and 645, making it one of the oldest Quran manuscripts to have survived."><img alt="Image 6Two leaves of an early Quranic manuscript in the Mingana Collection of Middle Eastern manuscripts of the University of Birmingham&#39;s Cadbury Research Library were discovered in 2015 as being dated between 568 and 645, making it one of the oldest Quran manuscripts to have survived." src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/Birmingham_Quran_manuscript.jpg/120px-Birmingham_Quran_manuscript.jpg" decoding="async" width="120" height="78" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/Birmingham_Quran_manuscript.jpg/180px-Birmingham_Quran_manuscript.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/Birmingham_Quran_manuscript.jpg/240px-Birmingham_Quran_manuscript.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2048" data-file-height="1333" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext"><span class="switcher-label" style="display:none"><span class="randomSlideshow-sr-only">Image 6</span></span><b><a href="/wiki/Birmingham_Quran_manuscript" title="Birmingham Quran manuscript">Two leaves</a></b> of an <a href="/wiki/Early_Quranic_manuscript" class="mw-redirect" title="Early Quranic manuscript">early Quranic manuscript</a> in the <a href="/wiki/Mingana_Collection" title="Mingana Collection">Mingana Collection</a> of Middle Eastern manuscripts of the <a href="/wiki/University_of_Birmingham" title="University of Birmingham">University of Birmingham</a>'s <a href="/wiki/Cadbury_Research_Library" class="mw-redirect" title="Cadbury Research Library">Cadbury Research Library</a> were discovered in 2015 as being dated between 568 and 645, making it one of the oldest <a href="/wiki/Quran" title="Quran">Quran</a> manuscripts to have survived.</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Marneuli_Imam_Ali_Mosque.JPG" class="mw-file-description" title="Image 7Imam Ali Mosque in Marneuli in Georgia Photograph: Zviad Avaliani"><img alt="Image 7Imam Ali Mosque in Marneuli in Georgia Photograph: Zviad Avaliani" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/Marneuli_Imam_Ali_Mosque.JPG/107px-Marneuli_Imam_Ali_Mosque.JPG" decoding="async" width="107" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/Marneuli_Imam_Ali_Mosque.JPG/160px-Marneuli_Imam_Ali_Mosque.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/Marneuli_Imam_Ali_Mosque.JPG/214px-Marneuli_Imam_Ali_Mosque.JPG 2x" data-file-width="2592" data-file-height="2912" /></a></span></div>
